Midtown Families: Here is a great resource in our community for food & clothing-

Harvest Compassion Center Phoenix / Maryvale has fed over 100,000 individuals.
The HCC strives to be more than just a local food bank, it‚Äôs a one-stop shopping experience! HCC‚Äôs look like mini-marts and clothing boutiques, where clients are welcomed to shop and choose their most-needed food, hygiene, baby and clothing items all FREE of charge.
With no pre-qualifications and/or appointments ever needed, HCC‚Äôs are open to the general public and provide service to anyone living in Arizona. Our desire is to welcome and love every client who walks through our doors offering them a first-class, dignified experience.

www.harvestcompassioncenter.org

During the COVID 19 Quarantine remember to have your kids wash their hands!

Here are when you and your kids should wash your hands:

- After you have been in a public place and touched an item or surface that may be frequently touched by other people, such as door handles, tables, gas pumps, shopping carts, or electronic cashier registers/screens, etc.

- Before touching your eyes, nose, or mouth because that‚Äôs how germs enter our bodies

post_text:
Dear Students & Families of Midtown Primary:

BREAKING NEWS:
Midtown Primary will Remained Closed Through the End of the School Year.
The Governor's Office and ADE has announced the closure of all AZ Schools through the rest of the school year.
Our learning will not stop, each of our teachers are dedicated to continue educating our students with daily online classes and take home packets.
Even though we can't be together at school - we are still here for you and your children. Please call if you have any questions or concerns 602-265-5133 ( we check our messages daily )
We Love & Miss you! We Got This! Midtown Dragons Rock!!

We will continue our Grab and Go meals!
Every Monday, Wednesday, Friday at these locations:
Midtown Primary School 8am -9am
Park Lee Apartments 9:30am - 10:30am

******We are offering food to anyone 18 years and younger. They do not have to be enrolled, but each child needs to be present to pick up their meals.
